A	O
pattern	O
recognition	O
system	O
particularly	O
useful	O
for	O
recognizing	O
speech	O
or	O
handwriting	O
.	O
An	O
input	O
signal	O
is	O
first	O
filtered	O
by	O
a	O
filter	O
bank	O
having	O
two	O
stages	O
where	O
the	O
outputs	O
of	O
the	O
first	O
stage	O
is	O
fed	O
forward	O
to	O
the	O
second	O
stage	O
of	O
a	O
significant	O
number	O
of	O
filters	O
and	O
the	O
output	O
of	O
the	O
second	O
stage	O
is	O
fed	O
back	O
to	O
the	O
first	O
stage	O
of	O
a	O
significant	O
number	O
of	O
the	O
filters	O
.	O
Such	O
feedback	O
enhances	O
the	O
signal-to-noise	O
ratio	O
and	O
resembles	O
the	O
coupling	O
between	O
the	O
different	O
sections	O
of	O
the	O
basilar	O
membrane	O
of	O
the	O
cochlear	O
.	O
The	O
output	O
of	O
the	O
filter	O
bank	O
is	O
a	O
two-dimensional	O
frequency-time	O
representation	O
of	O
the	O
original	O
signal	O
.	O
A	O
second	O
set	O
of	O
filters	O
which	O
takes	O
as	O
input	O
two-dimensional	O
signals	O
,	O
detects	O
the	O
presence	O
of	O
elementary	O
tonotopic	O
features	O
such	O
as	O
the	O
onset	O
,	O
rise	O
,	O
fall	O
and	O
frequency	O
of	O
any	O
significant	O
tones	O
in	O
a	O
speech	O
signal	O
.	O
A	O
third	O
set	O
of	O
filters	O
detects	O
any	O
contrasts	O
in	O
the	O
elementary	O
features	O
at	O
various	O
levels	O
of	O
resolution	O
.	O
After	O
such	O
filtering	O
,	O
a	O
neural	O
network	O
is	O
employed	O
to	O
learn	O
patterns	O
formed	O
from	O
the	O
multi-resolution	O
contrasts	O
in	O
the	O
identified	O
features	O
so	O
that	O
the	O
system	O
recognizes	O
symbols	O
from	O
an	O
input	O
signal	O
that	O
is	O
continuous	O
in	O
time	O
.	O
In	O
the	O
case	O
of	O
speech	O
,	O
the	O
system	O
recognizes	O
continuous	O
speech	O
in	O
a	O
speaker-independent	O
manner	O
,	O
and	O
is	O
also	O
tolerant	O
of	O
noise	O
.	O

