filtering	O
means	O
processes	O
the	O
first	O
filtering	O
means	O
output	O
to	O
provide	O
a	O
two-dimensional	O
representation	O
at	O
various	O
scales	O
or	O
resolutions	O
in	O
frequency	O
and	O
time	O
of	O
the	O
tonotopic	O
features	O
of	O
the	O
input	O
signal	O
.	O
The	O
features	O
preferably	O
include	O
onset	O
,	O
rise	O
and	O
fall	O
of	O
any	O
significant	O
tones	O
of	O
the	O
input	O
signal	O
in	O
the	O
two-dimensional	O
representation	O
.	O
In	O
a	O
further	O
improvement	O
,	O
the	O
tonotopic	O
features	O
also	O
indicate	O
frequency	O
of	O
any	O
significant	O
tones	O
of	O
the	O
input	O
signal	O
.	O

In	O
the	O
preferred	O
embodiment	O
where	O
the	O
input	O
signal	O
is	O
a	O
speech	O
signal	O
,	O
in	O
addition	O
to	O
the	O
first	O
and	O
